```

These classes represent the tables from your original question. You can also add additional properties to the models if needed, such as navigation properties to establish relationships between different models.

Once you have defined these models, you can use them in your ASP.NET MVC application to perform CRUD operations, display data to users, and handle user interactions.

Remember to also implement appropriate security measures, such as hashing and salting passwords, to protect user information in your application.

Yes, exactly. In a relational database, tables can have relationships with each other. These relationships can be one-to-one, one-to-many, or many-to-many.

In the context of your application, you can establish these relationships using navigation properties in your models. Navigation properties allow you to navigate and access related data between different models.

Here's an example of adding navigation properties to establish relationships between the models:

```csharp
