    public User User { get; set; }
    public Course Course { get; set; }
}
```

In this example, the `Enrollments` property in the `User` class creates a one-to-many relationship between a user and their enrollments. Similarly, the `Assignments` property in the `Course` class establishes a one-to-many relationship between a course and its assignments.

By using these navigation properties, you can easily access related data. For example, given a course object, you can access its associated assignments by accessing the `Assignments` property.

These navigation properties will be helpful when querying and manipulating data in your ASP.NET MVC application.

